  "soap_summary": "Patient with several days (about 5 days) of viral-like respiratory illness: dry cough (worse in morning) with minimal sputum, rhinorrhea, sore throat, mild ear fullness, subjective fevers/night sweats, brief diarrhea day 1 (now resolved), and myalgial stiffness in elbows/knees. Reports feeling very rundown. Past medical history: type 2 diabetes, raised blood pressure (hypertension), overweight. Current meds: metformin and occasional aspirin. Plan: conservative management (rest, fluids, paracetamol) and delayed/conditional antibiotic prescription (amoxicillin, 1 tablet TID) to start if not improving or still breathless after 24\u201348 hours; follow-up if still unwell next week.",
